⸻

Design principles

1. Preserve authorship

The user’s ink matters.
AI should not instantly replace their work with sterile typeset math unless asked.

2. Show transformations, not just outcomes

Math understanding lives in the transition.

3. Keep reversibility sacred

AI page edits must always be undoable.

4. Layer intuition with rigor

“Why” and “how” should both be available.

5. Adapt to skill level

A child, a college student, and a researcher should all be able to use the same surface differently.

